shedhand
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a worker in a shearing gang who does not shear, but acts as a helper, picker-up, broomie, rousie, presser or fleeecie.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:-
Pronunciation:
Notes: aka shed hand, shed-hand
